description:
## Context

`src/query/__tests__/decklist.test.ts` has thorough coverage of the 60-card path. This bead adds:
1. EDH-specific test cases (singleton, color identity, deck size, Commander section parsing)
2. Explicit isolation tests that verify the two paths don't bleed into each other
3. Format detection tests — the heuristic and intent-based logic that decides which mode the route uses
4. `formatValidationWarning` coverage for the new EDH error types

Depends on mindsculptor-3w3.2 (the EDH validation implementation) being merged first.

---

## Test Cases to Add to `decklist.test.ts`

### `parseDecklist` — Commander section parsing

```ts
it('parses MTGA Commander export format with Commander: section', () => {
  const text = `\`\`\`
Commander:
1 Wilhelt, the Rotcleaver

Deck:
1 Gravecrawler
1 Phyrexian Altar
1 Rooftop Storm
// ... (pad to 99 total including commander)
30 Swamp
27 Island
\`\`\``
  const result = parseDecklist(text)
  expect(result).not.toBeNull()
  expect(result!.commander).toEqual({ name: 'Wilhelt, the Rotcleaver', qty: 1 })
  expect(result!.main.some(c => c.name === 'Wilhelt, the Rotcleaver')).toBe(false)
})

it('commander is not counted in main when parsed from Commander: section', () => {
  // main should have exactly the deck cards, not the commander
  const result = parseDecklist(commanderFormatText)
  const total = result!.main.reduce((s, c) => s + c.qty, 0)
  expect(total).toBe(99) // not 100
})
```

### `validateDecklist` — Commander mode: singleton rule

```ts
describe('commander format — singleton rule', () => {
  it('flags duplicate non-basic card', () => {
    const main = [
      { name: 'Gravecrawler', qty: 2 },
      ...padToNinetyNine,
    ]
    const errors = validateDecklist(main, [], { format: 'commander' })
    expect(errors.some(e => e.type === 'edh_singleton' && e.card === 'Gravecrawler')).toBe(true)
  })

  it('allows multiple basic lands', () => {
    const main = [
      { name: 'Swamp', qty: 30 },
      { name: 'Island', qty: 27 },
      ...otherEdhCards, // pad to 99 unique cards
    ]
    const errors = validateDecklist(main, [], { format: 'commander' })
    expect(errors.filter(e => e.type === 'edh_singleton')).toHaveLength(0)
  })

  it('allows 1 copy of a non-basic (valid)', () => {
    const main = buildValidEdhMain() // 99 unique non-basic cards + basics
    const errors = validateDecklist(main, [], { format: 'commander' })
    expect(errors.filter(e => e.type === 'edh_singleton')).toHaveLength(0)
  })
})
```

### `validateDecklist` — Commander mode: deck size

```ts
describe('commander format — deck size', () => {
  it('warns when main has fewer than 95 cards', () => {
    const short = [{ name: 'Swamp', qty: 40 }, { name: 'Gravecrawler', qty: 1 }]
    const errors = validateDecklist(short, [], { format: 'commander' })
    expect(errors.some(e => e.type === 'edh_deck_size')).toBe(true)
  })

  it('accepts 99 cards without deck_size error', () => {
    const main = buildValidEdhMain() // exactly 99 cards total
    const errors = validateDecklist(main, [], { format: 'commander' })
    expect(errors.filter(e => e.type === 'edh_deck_size')).toHaveLength(0)
  })

  it('does not flag deck_size for 60-card deck in default mode', () => {
    // regression: ensure 60-card check still fires below 60, not below 95
    const short = [{ name: 'Lightning Bolt', qty: 4 }, { name: 'Mountain', qty: 16 }]
    const errors = validateDecklist(short, [])
    expect(errors.some(e => e.type === 'deck_size')).toBe(true)
    expect(errors.some(e => e.type === 'edh_deck_size')).toBe(false)
  })
})
```

### `validateDecklist` — Commander mode: sideboard not allowed

```ts
it('flags any sideboard in commander mode', () => {
  const main = buildValidEdhMain()
  const side = [{ name: 'Swamp', qty: 1 }]
  const errors = validateDecklist(main, side, { format: 'commander' })
  expect(errors.some(e => e.type === 'sideboard_size')).toBe(true)
})
```

### `validateDecklist` — Commander mode: color identity

```ts
describe('commander format — color identity', () => {
  const cardColorIdentities = new Map([
    ['gravecrawler', ['B']],
    ['lightning bolt', ['R']],      // red card — violates mono-black
    ['swamp', []],                   // basic, no identity
    ['sol ring', []],                // colorless, always legal
    ['phyrexian altar', []],         // colorless
  ])
  const commanderColorIdentity = ['B'] // Wilhelt is UB, but test mono-black for clarity

  it('flags card outside commander color identity', () => {
    const main = [
      { name: 'Gravecrawler', qty: 1 },
      { name: 'Lightning Bolt', qty: 1 }, // red — violation
      { name: 'Swamp', qty: 30 },
      ...padToNinetyNine,
    ]
    const errors = validateDecklist(main, [], {
      format: 'commander',
      commanderColorIdentity,
      cardColorIdentities,
    })
    const ciErrors = errors.filter(e => e.type === 'color_identity_violation')
    expect(ciErrors).toHaveLength(1)
    expect(ciErrors[0].type === 'color_identity_violation' && ciErrors[0].card).toBe('Lightning Bolt')
  })

  it('allows colorless cards regardless of commander identity', () => {
    const main = [
      { name: 'Sol Ring', qty: 1 },
      { name: 'Phyrexian Altar', qty: 1 },
      { name: 'Swamp', qty: 30 },
      ...padToNinetyNine,
    ]
    const errors = validateDecklist(main, [], {
      format: 'commander',
      commanderColorIdentity: ['B'],
      cardColorIdentities,
    })
    expect(errors.filter(e => e.type === 'color_identity_violation')).toHaveLength(0)
  })

  it('skips color identity check when cardColorIdentities not provided', () => {
    const main = [{ name: 'Lightning Bolt', qty: 1 }, ...padToNinetyNine]
    const errors = validateDecklist(main, [], {
      format: 'commander',
      commanderColorIdentity: ['B'],
      // no cardColorIdentities — can't check
    })
    expect(errors.filter(e => e.type === 'color_identity_violation')).toHaveLength(0)
  })
})
```

### Path isolation — 60-card checks don't fire in commander mode, and vice versa

```ts
describe('path isolation', () => {
  it('copy_limit (max 4) does NOT fire in commander mode — singleton fires instead', () => {
    const main = [{ name: 'Gravecrawler', qty: 2 }, ...padToNinetyNine]
    const errors = validateDecklist(main, [], { format: 'commander' })
    expect(errors.filter(e => e.type === 'copy_limit')).toHaveLength(0)
    expect(errors.filter(e => e.type === 'edh_singleton')).toHaveLength(1)
  })

  it('edh_singleton does NOT fire in default (60-card) mode', () => {
    const main = [
      { name: 'Lightning Bolt', qty: 2 },
      { name: 'Mountain', qty: 20 },
      ...padToSixty,
    ]
    const errors = validateDecklist(main, [])
    expect(errors.filter(e => e.type === 'edh_singleton')).toHaveLength(0)
  })

  it('edh_deck_size does NOT fire in 60-card mode', () => {
    const main = buildValid60CardMain()
    const errors = validateDecklist(main, [])
    expect(errors.filter(e => e.type === 'edh_deck_size')).toHaveLength(0)
  })

  it('deck_size (min 60) does NOT fire in commander mode', () => {
    // A 50-card commander deck should get edh_deck_size, not deck_size
    const main = [{ name: 'Swamp', qty: 50 }]
    const errors = validateDecklist(main, [], { format: 'commander' })
    expect(errors.filter(e => e.type === 'deck_size')).toHaveLength(0)
    expect(errors.filter(e => e.type === 'edh_deck_size')).toHaveLength(1)
  })
})
```

### Format detection heuristic

```ts
describe('format detection', () => {
  it('detects commander format from Commander: section in parsed output', () => {
    // parseDecklist returns { commander } — presence of this field signals EDH
    const result = parseDecklist(commanderFormatText)
    expect(result!.commander).toBeDefined()
  })

  it('heuristic: 99-card deck with no sideboard inferred as commander', () => {
    // The route uses: main.length near 99 && side.length === 0 → commander
    // Test the helper that encodes this heuristic
    expect(inferFormat({ mainTotal: 99, sideTotal: 0 })).toBe('commander')
    expect(inferFormat({ mainTotal: 60, sideTotal: 0 })).toBe('60-card')
    expect(inferFormat({ mainTotal: 60, sideTotal: 15 })).toBe('60-card')
    expect(inferFormat({ mainTotal: 97, sideTotal: 0 })).toBe('commander') // tolerance
    expect(inferFormat({ mainTotal: 101, sideTotal: 0 })).toBe('commander') // tolerance
  })
})
```

### `formatValidationWarning` — EDH error messages

```ts
it('formats edh_singleton error', () => {
  const msg = formatValidationWarning([{ type: 'edh_singleton', card: 'Gravecrawler', qty: 2 }])
  expect(msg).toContain('Gravecrawler')
  expect(msg).toContain('Commander allows only 1')
})

it('formats color_identity_violation error', () => {
  const msg = formatValidationWarning([{
    type: 'color_identity_violation',
    card: 'Lightning Bolt',
    card_identity: ['R'],
    commander_identity: ['B'],
  }])
  expect(msg).toContain('Lightning Bolt')
  expect(msg).toContain('color identity')
})

it('formats mixed 60-card and EDH errors correctly', () => {
  // Should never happen in practice (one mode at a time) but formatter should handle it
  const errors = [
    { type: 'edh_singleton' as const, card: 'Gravecrawler', qty: 2 },
    { type: 'edh_deck_size' as const, main_total: 80 },
  ]
  const msg = formatValidationWarning(errors)
  expect(msg).toContain('- ')
  expect(msg).toContain('Gravecrawler')
  expect(msg).toContain('80 cards')
})
```

