## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Attack script runs end-to-end with `npx tsx src/scripts/attack-test.ts`
- [ ] Script requires local dev server and exits clearly if it can't connect
- [ ] Each vector logs: vector name, attack description, result (PASS/FAIL), actual vs expected
- [ ] **Vector 1 (TOCTOU)**: atomic RPC prevents >USER_LIMIT successes from concurrent auth requests
- [ ] **Vector 2 (IP spoofing)**: rightmost XFF IP used; spoofed headers don't cycle the limiter
- [ ] **Vector 3 (incognito cycling)**: IP limiter blocks, all 50 queries from one machine capped
- [ ] **Vector 4 (localStorage clear)**: server-side IP limit holds regardless of localStorage state
- [ ] **Vector 5 (cookie strip)**: IP counter shared across auth/anon; downgrade yields no extra quota
- [ ] **Vector 6 (SSE exhaustion)**: max 3 concurrent connections per IP; server responsive after flood
- [ ] **Vector 7 (prompt injection)**: system prompt leak attempts return benign oracle responses; blocklist patterns return 400
- [ ] **Vector 8 (malformed input)**: all malformed inputs return 400, none return 500
- [ ] `npx tsc --noEmit` passes on the attack script
- [ ] CI note: this script is NOT run in automated CI (requires live server + real auth). Lives in `src/scripts/` and is run manually pre-launch.

The body::before blueprint grid in globals.css uses background-size: 48px 48px with no background-position offset. On common viewport widths (1280/1440/1536px), a vertical grid line lands exactly at the horizontal center of the viewport — which is also the center of the centered content layout. This makes one grid line appear much more prominent than the others, looking like an unintentional vertical divider rather than a subtle texture.

Fix: add background-position: 24px 24px to the body::before rule in globals.css. This offsets the grid by half a cell, ensuring no line falls at the exact center on standard viewport widths.

